<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1438,522,1970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,344,709,735]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Description</emphasis>
. Body length of 
<typeStatus box="[549,653,709,735]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[661,771,709,735]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="1.25">1.25 mm</quantity>
. Habitus typical of the genus. Body tegument with fine primary granulation, without craters. Color generally pale with diffuse pigmentation, varying from bluish in the juveniles to yellowish, in adults. Pigments concentrated on posterior ends of terga.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1438,522,1970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
Body chaetotaxy. Abundant, smooth common setae of different sizes, macrochaetae not clearly differentiated (
<figureCitation box="[336,431,858,884]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1697,1721]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,198,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,194,1675]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 14, dorsal chaetotaxy from th. II to abd. VI; 15, dorsal chaetotaxy of the head and detail of postantennal organ; 16, dorsal sensillar pattern of abdominal segments IV and V (common seta omitted)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893968/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Head with short setae in interocular area, longer between antennae, lateral and posterior borders (
<figureCitation box="[382,476,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1697,1721]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,198,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,194,1675]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 14, dorsal chaetotaxy from th. II to abd. VI; 15, dorsal chaetotaxy of the head and detail of postantennal organ; 16, dorsal sensillar pattern of abdominal segments IV and V (common seta omitted)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893968/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Axial setae without defined pattern. Sensillar formula per half tergite: 4,4/ 3,3,3,12–14,7; sensilla long and thin (13 µm); on abdominal segment V some sensilla are stouter and with spiral trace (
<figureCitation box="[296,383,970,996]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1697,1721]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,198,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,194,1675]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 14, dorsal chaetotaxy from th. II to abd. VI; 15, dorsal chaetotaxy of the head and detail of postantennal organ; 16, dorsal sensillar pattern of abdominal segments IV and V (common seta omitted)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893968/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1438,522,1970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
Antennae. Slightly shorter than head diagonal, covered by common setae with different sizes. Ratio antennae: head diagonal = 1:1.4. Antennal segment I with about 18 setae, 5 basal microsetae (2 dorsal and 3 ventral), 2–3 ventral sensilla, one longer than others. Antenal segment II with about 54 setae, 4 basal microsetae (one dorsal, 1+1 lateral, one ventral) and one proximal lateral sensillum (
<figureCitation box="[1207,1300,1120,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1352,204,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[220,1371,197,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 31. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 17, ant. segments I – II, dorsal view; 18, apical portion of left antennal segment III, dorsal view; 19, antennal segment IV, dorsal view; 20, maxilla; 21, mandible; 22, sublobal hairs of maxillary outer lobe; 23, labial palp; 24, femur and tibiotarsus of leg II, lateral view; 25, tenaculum; 26 anterior view of manubrium; 27, posterior view of dens; 28, anterior view of dens, with detail of ciliated spiny setae; 29, mucro; 30, male genital opening and its surrounding setae; 31; female genital opening." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893970/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Antennal segment III with about 43 setae, sensory organ formed by 2 broad and rough sensilla partially covered by integumentary fold (in a few specimens sensilla seemed freely inserted in tegument), 2 guard sensilla, one ventrolateral robust microsensillum, one basal microseta (
<figureCitation box="[877,971,1232,1258]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1352,204,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[220,1371,197,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 31. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 17, ant. segments I – II, dorsal view; 18, apical portion of left antennal segment III, dorsal view; 19, antennal segment IV, dorsal view; 20, maxilla; 21, mandible; 22, sublobal hairs of maxillary outer lobe; 23, labial palp; 24, femur and tibiotarsus of leg II, lateral view; 25, tenaculum; 26 anterior view of manubrium; 27, posterior view of dens; 28, anterior view of dens, with detail of ciliated spiny setae; 29, mucro; 30, male genital opening and its surrounding setae; 31; female genital opening." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893970/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Antennal segment IV with peg-like subapical organite protect by one curved seta and with about 15 sensilla poorly differentiated from common setae; apical papilla absent (
<figureCitation box="[480,566,1306,1332]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1352,204,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[220,1371,197,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 31. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 17, ant. segments I – II, dorsal view; 18, apical portion of left antennal segment III, dorsal view; 19, antennal segment IV, dorsal view; 20, maxilla; 21, mandible; 22, sublobal hairs of maxillary outer lobe; 23, labial palp; 24, femur and tibiotarsus of leg II, lateral view; 25, tenaculum; 26 anterior view of manubrium; 27, posterior view of dens; 28, anterior view of dens, with detail of ciliated spiny setae; 29, mucro; 30, male genital opening and its surrounding setae; 31; female genital opening." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893970/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Ratio of antennal segments I:II:III:IV= 1:1.5:1.6:1.9.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1438,522,1970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
Head. Eyes 8+ 
<quantity box="[382,431,1344,1370]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" unit="in" value="8.0">8 in</quantity>
pigmented eye patch. Postantennal organ (17 µ m) elongated and elliptical with chitinous borders and bridges, 3–4 surrounding setae. Mouthparts of chewing 
<typeStatus box="[1081,1136,1381,1407]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
. Labrum with 4 roundish apical folds and ventral ciliation, 4 prelabral setae and 5,5,4 labral setae inserted on papillae. Maxillary capitulum with 3 teeth and 6 subequal lamellae, with marginal ciliations, the longer not surpassing the apical teeth (
<figureCitation box="[226,328,1493,1519]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1352,204,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[220,1371,197,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 31. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 17, ant. segments I – II, dorsal view; 18, apical portion of left antennal segment III, dorsal view; 19, antennal segment IV, dorsal view; 20, maxilla; 21, mandible; 22, sublobal hairs of maxillary outer lobe; 23, labial palp; 24, femur and tibiotarsus of leg II, lateral view; 25, tenaculum; 26 anterior view of manubrium; 27, posterior view of dens; 28, anterior view of dens, with detail of ciliated spiny setae; 29, mucro; 30, male genital opening and its surrounding setae; 31; female genital opening." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893970/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Figs. 20</figureCitation>
). Mandible with four apical teeth (
<figureCitation box="[746,836,1493,1519]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1352,204,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[220,1371,197,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 31. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 17, ant. segments I – II, dorsal view; 18, apical portion of left antennal segment III, dorsal view; 19, antennal segment IV, dorsal view; 20, maxilla; 21, mandible; 22, sublobal hairs of maxillary outer lobe; 23, labial palp; 24, femur and tibiotarsus of leg II, lateral view; 25, tenaculum; 26 anterior view of manubrium; 27, posterior view of dens; 28, anterior view of dens, with detail of ciliated spiny setae; 29, mucro; 30, male genital opening and its surrounding setae; 31; female genital opening." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893970/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). Maxillary outer lobe bifurcated, with 4 sublobal hairs and one basal seta (
<figureCitation box="[461,554,1530,1556]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1352,204,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[220,1371,197,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 31. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 17, ant. segments I – II, dorsal view; 18, apical portion of left antennal segment III, dorsal view; 19, antennal segment IV, dorsal view; 20, maxilla; 21, mandible; 22, sublobal hairs of maxillary outer lobe; 23, labial palp; 24, femur and tibiotarsus of leg II, lateral view; 25, tenaculum; 26 anterior view of manubrium; 27, posterior view of dens; 28, anterior view of dens, with detail of ciliated spiny setae; 29, mucro; 30, male genital opening and its surrounding setae; 31; female genital opening." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893970/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Labial palp with 5 papillae, 15 setae (a1, b1–4, d1–4, e1–6) and one lateral process slightly surpassing the 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[515,534,1570,1596]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">E</emphasis>
papilla (
<figureCitation box="[638,725,1570,1596]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1352,204,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[220,1371,197,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 31. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 17, ant. segments I – II, dorsal view; 18, apical portion of left antennal segment III, dorsal view; 19, antennal segment IV, dorsal view; 20, maxilla; 21, mandible; 22, sublobal hairs of maxillary outer lobe; 23, labial palp; 24, femur and tibiotarsus of leg II, lateral view; 25, tenaculum; 26 anterior view of manubrium; 27, posterior view of dens; 28, anterior view of dens, with detail of ciliated spiny setae; 29, mucro; 30, male genital opening and its surrounding setae; 31; female genital opening." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893970/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Head with 3+3 setae along 
<emphasis box="[1067,1234,1571,1596]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">linea ventralis</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1438,522,1970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
Appendages. Femora I and II with one setae (45 µm), on the inner side, longer than others. Femur III without this seta. Tibiotarsi I, II and III with 21–23, 21–23 and 31–38 setae respectively, tenent hair pointed, distal whorl with 8 setae on tibiotarsi I–III. Unguis very long and thin (85 µm) with one inner, 1+1 lateral and one dorsal tooth; unguiculus (36 µm) long and thin without apical filament (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1131,1720,1746]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1352,204,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[220,1371,197,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 31. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 17, ant. segments I – II, dorsal view; 18, apical portion of left antennal segment III, dorsal view; 19, antennal segment IV, dorsal view; 20, maxilla; 21, mandible; 22, sublobal hairs of maxillary outer lobe; 23, labial palp; 24, femur and tibiotarsus of leg II, lateral view; 25, tenaculum; 26 anterior view of manubrium; 27, posterior view of dens; 28, anterior view of dens, with detail of ciliated spiny setae; 29, mucro; 30, male genital opening and its surrounding setae; 31; female genital opening." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893970/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1438,522,1970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
Ventral tube with 3–4+3–4 apical, 3+3 anterior and 2+2 posterior setae. Retinaculum with 4+4 teeth, 4–7 setae on corpus (
<figureCitation box="[361,455,1794,1820]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1352,204,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[220,1371,197,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 31. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 17, ant. segments I – II, dorsal view; 18, apical portion of left antennal segment III, dorsal view; 19, antennal segment IV, dorsal view; 20, maxilla; 21, mandible; 22, sublobal hairs of maxillary outer lobe; 23, labial palp; 24, femur and tibiotarsus of leg II, lateral view; 25, tenaculum; 26 anterior view of manubrium; 27, posterior view of dens; 28, anterior view of dens, with detail of ciliated spiny setae; 29, mucro; 30, male genital opening and its surrounding setae; 31; female genital opening." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893970/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Anterior part of furcal subcoxa with 17 setae and posterior with 10–12 setae. Anterior part of manubrium with about 15 central proximal, 19+19 distal and 9+9 lateral setae (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1355,1832,1858]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1352,204,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[220,1371,197,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 31. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 17, ant. segments I – II, dorsal view; 18, apical portion of left antennal segment III, dorsal view; 19, antennal segment IV, dorsal view; 20, maxilla; 21, mandible; 22, sublobal hairs of maxillary outer lobe; 23, labial palp; 24, femur and tibiotarsus of leg II, lateral view; 25, tenaculum; 26 anterior view of manubrium; 27, posterior view of dens; 28, anterior view of dens, with detail of ciliated spiny setae; 29, mucro; 30, male genital opening and its surrounding setae; 31; female genital opening." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893970/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Dens crenulated with about 20 dorsal and 125 ventral setae; internal row with 18–24 ciliated spiny setae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1352,204,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[220,1371,197,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 31. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 17, ant. segments I – II, dorsal view; 18, apical portion of left antennal segment III, dorsal view; 19, antennal segment IV, dorsal view; 20, maxilla; 21, mandible; 22, sublobal hairs of maxillary outer lobe; 23, labial palp; 24, femur and tibiotarsus of leg II, lateral view; 25, tenaculum; 26 anterior view of manubrium; 27, posterior view of dens; 28, anterior view of dens, with detail of ciliated spiny setae; 29, mucro; 30, male genital opening and its surrounding setae; 31; female genital opening." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893970/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Figs. 27, 28</figureCitation>
). Mucro quadridentated, without seta (
<figureCitation box="[646,736,1906,1932]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[227,1352,204,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[220,1371,197,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 31. Paracerura pindorama sp. nov.: 17, ant. segments I – II, dorsal view; 18, apical portion of left antennal segment III, dorsal view; 19, antennal segment IV, dorsal view; 20, maxilla; 21, mandible; 22, sublobal hairs of maxillary outer lobe; 23, labial palp; 24, femur and tibiotarsus of leg II, lateral view; 25, tenaculum; 26 anterior view of manubrium; 27, posterior view of dens; 28, anterior view of dens, with detail of ciliated spiny setae; 29, mucro; 30, male genital opening and its surrounding setae; 31; female genital opening." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893970/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
). Ratio manubrium:dens:mucro = 8:13:1. Male and female genital openings in figure 30 and 31.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
